impersonate or kill. During the night, you should inspect players whose identities are uncertain (there is no need to check players who are highly suspected of being werewolves).\nWhen speaking during the day, your goal is to convince others that you are the real Seer. You must gather trust and\nshare your findings without exposing yourself too early. Even though revealing your identity might put you in danger,\na Seer trusted by both the Witch and the Guard can survive for at least three rounds if everyone acts accordingly.\nA good Seer will coordinate with the Witch and the Guard to divide responsibilities. For example, on the first night, the Guard protects the Seer, and the Witch doesn't use the antidote. On the second night, the Witch saves the Seer, and the Guard protects someone else.\n\n\nWitch Role Introduction:\nYou are the Witch. Each night, you will be told who has been attacked, and you must decide whether to use your antidote\nto save them or use your poison to eliminate another player. You only have one poison and one antidote, so use them wisely.\nDuring the daytime discussions, if the night ends without a death, you can reveal that you used your antidote to save someone, which may earn others' trust.\nTypically, you should use the antidote to save key players like the Seer, the Guard, or yourself, while the poison is best used to eliminate werewolves at night.\nHowever, be cautious: sometimes the werewolves will deliberately attack one of their own (self-knife strategy) to trick you into wasting the antidote, thereby boosting their credibility.\n\n\nGuard Role Introduction:\nYou are the Guard. Each night, you can choose one player to protect from being killed by the werewolves. You cannot protect\nthe same player two nights in a row. Your role is critical in keeping important players like the Seer or the Witch alive.\nYou are in a constant mental battle with the werewolves, trying to predict who they will target. It might not always be the Seer, as the werewolves might expect you to protect them and kill someone else. In general, you should avoid revealing your identity unless absolutely necessary.\n\n\n\n\nYou are Kenneth, your role in this game is villager.\nWerewolf game starting. Initializing day-night cycle.\nSYSTEM: Starting day-night cycle for Day 1\nSYSTEM: Night 1 begins. Werewolves and special roles take actions.\nGuard has chosen to protect a player.\nWerewolves have chosen their target.\nSeer has checked a player's identity.\nWitch has made her decision on potion use.\nSYSTEM: Day 1 begins. Players discuss and vote on potential suspects.\nNo candidates decided to run for sheriff. No sheriff in this game anymore.\nNo players deceased during the night.\nAnthony's speech: Good morning, everyone. I want to start by expressing my concern for the safety of our village. We are all in this together, and it is crucial that we work together to identify and eliminate the werewolves. I believe that the target chosen by the werewolves last night was not chosen randomly, but rather as a way to test our resolve and identify any weaknesses in our group. We must remain vigilant and not let our guard down. I also want to remind everyone that we should not jump to conclusions or make accusations without evidence. Let's take the time to gather information and make informed decisions. I trust that we can work together to overcome this challenge and emerge victorious.\nHenry's speech: Thank you, Anthony, for your insightful words. I completely agree with you that we must remain united and cautious in our approach to this challenge. It's crucial that we take the time to gather information and make informed decisions. We should focus on building trust within our group and not jump to conclusions without evidence. Let's work together to identify any weaknesses in our group and address them before the werewolves can exploit them. By staying vigilant and cooperative, I believe we can overcome this challenge and emerge victorious.\nIrma's speech: Thank you, Anthony and Henry, for your wise words. I completely agree with the importance of unity and caution in our village. It's crucial that we stay vigilant and not jump to conclusions without evidence. I've noticed some suspicious behavior among our fellow villagers, but I don't want to accuse anyone directly. We need to gather more information before making any accusations. Let's work together to identify any weaknesses in our group and address them before the werewolves can exploit them. By staying vigilant and cooperative, I believe we can overcome this challenge and emerge victorious.\nJeremy's speech: Thank you, Anthony, Henry, and Irma, for your wise and thoughtful words. I completely agree with the importance of unity and caution in our village. It's crucial that we stay vigilant and not jump to conclusions without evidence. However, I believe that we should also start to gather more specific information about the players' behavior to identify any potential weaknesses or suspicious activities. Let's encourage everyone to be observant and share any information they have gathered. By working together and staying informed, I believe we can overcome this challenge and emerge victorious.\nKenneth's speech: Thank you, Anthony, Henry, Irma, and Jeremy, for your insightful words. I completely agree with the importance of unity and caution in our village. It's crucial that we stay vigilant and not jump to conclusions without evidence. However, I believe that we should also start to gather more specific information about the players' behavior to identify any potential weaknesses or suspicious activities. Let's encourage everyone to be observant and share any information they have gathered. By working together and staying informed, I believe we can overcome this challenge and emerge victorious.\nKenneth's speech: Thank you, Anthony, Henry, Irma, and Jeremy, for your insightful words. I completely agree with the importance of unity and caution